  "title": "Team Lead, Restructuring and Forensics",
  "description": "<ul><li>Participate and lead in the day-to-day administration of corporate insolvency and restructuring engagements</li><li>Reviewing draft letters, notices, emails and reports</li><li>Securing, indexing and safekeeping of books and records.</li><li>Planning and executing assets realization / debt recovery process</li><li>Information gathering from books / records of clients and third parties</li><li>Managing the processes of adjudication of creditors' claims and the investigatory work to trace assets and assess potential recoveries for creditors</li><li>Participating in the financial review and preparing restructuring proposals</li><li>Liaising with stakeholders, creditors and other business advisors.</li><li>Participating in clients' / creditors' meetings and preparation of minutes of meetings</li><li>Coaching and guiding junior team members</li><li>Performing any other duties as assigned to support departmental and organization objectives</li><li>Working closely with Directors and Partners and communicate issue(s) aroused clearly and timely</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Accountancy, Law or other professional accounting qualifications recognised by ISCA</li><li>4 to 5 years of experience in corporate insolvency and restructuring, with strong insolvency technical knowledge and leadership experience in a professional services environment</li><li>Excellent project management, analytical, and financial modelling skills.</li><li>Strong written and verbal communication, including report writing and stakeholder presentations.</li><li>Able to work in a fast-paced environment and manage multiple deadlines</li><li>A strong team player and able to lead a small team</li></ul>",
